headline: Valero Energy vs. Phillips 66: Which Refining Stock Should You Bet On?
summary: VLO and PSX are set to gain as softer crude prices lift refining margins. However, PSX's diversified business model and exposure beyond refining stand out.

headline: Return of Venezuelan crude could cut US fuel oil imports
summary: BENGALURU/LONDON Jan 27 (Reuters) - U. demand for imported fuel oil is set to fall this year as refiners snap up new flows of heavy Venezuelan crude, ​yielding more domestically produced fuel oil that can be processed into higher-value products such as gasoline and ‌diesel.

headline: Phillips 66: Finally Positioned For A Refining Up-Cycle (With A Venezuela Kicker)
summary: Phillips 66 refining rebounds on lower costs, record utilization, and cheap heavy crude. See why I rate the PSX stock a Hold.
